Virginia Polytechnic Institute
VPI-V-0059491

Flora of Virginia
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brum.
near Stokesville, Augusta Co.

Scattered colonies for .7 mi. along
S bank of North River ca. 3/4 mi. SW of
Camp Thay Flather. With *Gaultheria*, *Epigaea*,
*Kalmia* & *Menziesia* under *Pinus strobus*, *Tsuga*
& *Acer rubrum*.
(Stokesville Quad.)                                          el. 1650 ft.
Charles E. Stevens                                          May 1, 1982
